a:3:{s:11:"notes_total";i:6;s:11:"notes_ctree";a:6:{i:0;a:32:{s:2:"id";i:44;s:5:"title";s:76:"Scoro schedules subtasks rollout for February 2026, with new planning logic";s:4:"href";s:93:"http://weekcrm.com/blog/all/scoro-schedules-subtasks-rollout-for-february-2026-with-new-plan/";s:13:"href-original";s:93:"http://weekcrm.com/blog/all/scoro-schedules-subtasks-rollout-for-february-2026-with-new-plan/";s:4:"time";a:2:{i:0;i:1769000400;i:1;a:2:{s:6:"offset";i:18000;s:6:"is_dst";b:0;}}s:13:"last-modified";a:2:{i:0;i:1768568053;i:1;a:2:{s:6:"offset";i:18000;s:6:"is_dst";b:0;}}s:4:"text";s:566:"<p>Scoro plans to introduce subtasks starting in February 2026 via a staged rollout. Alongside subtasks, Scoro will add work planning methods that control how budgeted hours and planned hours interact.</p>
<p>Rollout details:</p>
<p>Gradual release to groups of sites</p>
<p>Admin notification when available (in-app prompt)</p>
<p>No automatic workflow changes—existing setup remains until a team opts in</p>
<p>Learn more here: <a href="https://www.scoro.com/blog/scoro-version-update-26-1/">https://www.scoro.com/blog/scoro-version-update-26-1/</a></p>
